<br>
Of course you can't have any other melee nearby, but it's simple to keep a mob alive when they have in some cases well over 32k hp.<br>
<br>
I don't think charm should be completely nerfed because there are valid uses for it, however it needs to be balanced out.<br>
<br>
That might include disallowing heals or buffs on charmed pets, and adding a large slow to the higher level charms, like 30-50%.  That would bring their damage down to a reasonable range, of course you could still use them to tank, the best solution for that issue would be to increase mob sensitivity to aggro from people not in range so that a pet can't hold aggro for very long while everyone shoots arrows or whatever. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drenesh>Drenesh</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://pages.prodigy.net/bestsmileys1/emoticons1/reaper2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/03 12:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1874.topic&index=43>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://gyrene.com/survival/assets/nerdinside.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm leads to a sad day for tanks</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>On the token about taunts my necro pet at 54 *using the 49th pet not the rogue pet he gets owned on direct mellee* can hold taunt just fine i have to play my spells right so i dont grab aggro , But with real tanks all casters have to do that anyhow <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
